      "content": "The overrepresentation of specific racial groups in the prison and criminal justice system can largely be attributed to systemic racism, socio-economic disparities, and biased law enforcement practices. Racial profiling, harsher sentencing for minorities, and unequal access to quality legal representation contribute to these disparities. Additionally, historical and structural inequalities, such as redlining and discriminatory housing policies, have led to concentrated poverty and limited opportunities for marginalized communities. These factors collectively perpetuate a cycle of criminalization and incarceration among certain racial groups.",
